WEBVTT

00:48.642 --> 00:49.784
Merry Christmas, everybody.

00:49.924 --> 00:54.010
I'm so grateful you're here today, and I hope you're having an incredible Christmas season.

00:54.530 --> 00:58.176
I know at the Pettis House, our four boys can hardly wait for Christmas day.

00:58.196 --> 01:02.341
I hope and pray you're also enjoying our Christmas at Highlands experience.

01:02.822 --> 01:04.224
It's an honor to have you here.

01:04.865 --> 01:12.215
Before we go any further, I want to take a moment to thank the incredible team behind today's service, especially our music production and creative teams.

01:12.716 --> 01:16.882
For months, they have poured their heart and soul into what we're experiencing.

01:17.122 --> 01:21.167
Highlands is truly blessed with some of the most gifted people on the planet.

01:21.707 --> 01:31.159
I also want to take a moment to thank the thousands of Dream Teamers serving across all of our campuses today, parking cars, making hot chocolate, welcoming families, loving people.

01:31.619 --> 01:33.702
Dream Team, you are incredible.

01:34.182 --> 01:37.606
And to our entire Highlands family, Jill and I love you so much.

01:38.047 --> 01:42.512
We are praying for you every single day, especially in this Christmas season.

01:42.832 --> 01:44.274
You mean the world to us.

01:44.546 --> 01:49.853
And finally, if today is your first time with us, let me say on behalf of all of us, welcome.

01:50.094 --> 01:51.856
We are so excited you're here.

01:52.176 --> 01:55.180
And if you're looking for a church family, I hope you found one.

01:55.761 --> 02:03.291
From the very beginning of Highlands in 2001, our church has been built on a purpose far bigger than launching another service or opening another campus.

02:03.912 --> 02:11.863
From day one, our passion has been to help people answer the question every human heart eventually asks, is this all that there is?

02:12.985 --> 02:14.066
There has to be more.

02:14.498 --> 02:17.863
More to life, more to faith, and more to church.

02:18.424 --> 02:22.831
That's why our foundational verse as a church is Habakkuk 3 19.

02:23.692 --> 02:25.134
The sovereign Lord is my strength.

02:25.615 --> 02:27.357
He makes my feet like the feet of a deer.

02:27.978 --> 02:30.642
He enables me to tread on the heights.

02:31.624 --> 02:33.867
This verse is God's way of reminding us.

02:34.608 --> 02:40.137
He has more for us, more for our lives, more for our families, and more for our faith.

02:40.497 --> 02:43.762
This verse also reminds us that the more God has for us,

02:43.874 --> 02:45.256
doesn't happen all at once.

02:45.837 --> 02:47.519
It happens one step at a time.

02:48.100 --> 02:56.012
God has a spiritual journey for all of us, and helping people take next steps on that journey is our deepest passion as a church.

02:56.713 --> 03:08.050
The first step on that journey is when we come to truly know God, not just know about Him, but know Him personally, intimately, so that our relationship with Him becomes the highlight of our lives.

03:08.482 --> 03:10.704
As we walk with Him, we begin to find freedom.

03:10.784 --> 03:12.406
Freedom from the things that hold us back.

03:12.806 --> 03:15.489
Freedom from the shame and regret of yesterday.

03:15.509 --> 03:19.513
Freedom to become the person God always intended us to be.

03:20.094 --> 03:23.317
And as He frees us, we start to discover purpose.

03:23.837 --> 03:28.362
Because when God made you, He made you on purpose and with a purpose.

03:28.802 --> 03:33.067
There's a calling inside of you and it is never too late to live out that calling.

03:33.507 --> 03:36.530
And all of that leads to a life that makes a difference.

03:36.738 --> 03:45.889
a life that matters, a life of eternal impact, not just here at church serving on a team, but all week long in our homes, our workplaces, and our world.

03:46.630 --> 03:50.875
This is the journey God invites us into, and it's the journey we're on here at Highlands.

03:51.416 --> 03:55.921
This is the more that God has for all of us, and that includes you.

03:56.542 --> 04:01.688
If that resonates with something on the inside, then come be a part of this journey with us.

04:02.169 --> 04:06.354
I believe 2026 is gonna be the most powerful year ever for our church.

04:06.754 --> 04:12.741
On the first Sunday of the year, January 4th, we're launching a brand new message series to help you start the year strong.

04:13.202 --> 04:18.808
And that day will also begin 21 days of prayer, one of the most life-changing seasons of the year.

04:19.209 --> 04:23.273
I promise you don't want to miss all that God has in store.

04:24.074 --> 04:30.081
Now, before our candlelighting moment, I want to take just a few minutes and share a Christmas message from God's Word.

04:30.782 --> 04:34.066
Over the past few months, as I've prayed and prepared for our time together,

04:34.242 --> 04:40.111
I've come back to the Christmas story again and again, and it never ceases to amaze me.

04:40.652 --> 05:03.506
This story has everything, angels breaking through the night sky, proclaiming good news to shepherds watching their flocks, wise men traveling across distant lands, a young, unwed, pregnant couple, putting their entire trust in God, a guiding star, a humble stable, at the very center, a manger, cradling the greatest gift ever given, God's Son,

05:03.970 --> 05:05.672
the Savior of the world.

05:06.373 --> 05:10.178
As I've read through the story, I have found myself asking questions you may have asked.

05:10.799 --> 05:12.622
Why did it all happen this way?

05:13.062 --> 05:17.528
And maybe even more importantly, what does this story mean for us today?

05:18.229 --> 05:23.636
To answer those questions, we actually need to look back hundreds, even thousands of years before that major.

05:24.137 --> 05:27.602
Because believe it or not, the Christmas story didn't begin in Bethlehem.

05:28.182 --> 05:33.810
It actually began the moment sin entered the world and our relationship with God was broken.

05:34.210 --> 05:37.634
From that moment on, God set a rescue plan into motion.

05:38.155 --> 05:45.884
We see glimpses of it all throughout Scripture, but one of the clearest is found in the Old Testament in the book of Isaiah, Isaiah 118.

05:46.445 --> 05:55.276
Come now, let us reason together says the Lord, though your sins are like scarlet, they shall be white as snow, though they are as red as crimson, they shall be like wool.

05:56.157 --> 06:00.082
So you may be wondering why I am standing here in this field.

06:00.482 --> 06:05.630
Well, this is actually very similar to one you might have found in Israel in the time of Jesus.

06:06.090 --> 06:14.203
Staining right here, I can imagine, and I want you to imagine with me, the shepherds watching their sheep on that night that Jesus was born.

06:14.984 --> 06:17.548
All throughout the Bible, God uses sheep to describe us.

06:17.968 --> 06:21.353
And honestly, it would be offensive if it wasn't kind of true.

06:21.914 --> 06:25.299
Sheep wander off, sheep get stuck in places they have, no business being.

06:25.820 --> 06:29.906
Sheep will literally follow each other off a cliff, and as cute as they can be,

06:30.210 --> 06:31.973
They are pretty helpless on their own.

06:32.814 --> 06:37.421
God is telling us in Isaiah that like sheep, we cannot cleanse ourselves.

06:38.142 --> 06:39.484
We cannot rescue ourselves.

06:40.145 --> 06:44.592
Sin leaves a stain deeper than effort, resolve, or religion can reach.

06:45.453 --> 06:52.023
When this verse says our lives will become white as wool, it would have confounded the Jewish people.

06:52.383 --> 06:59.634
You see, scarlet and crimson, they're the deepest, most permanent dies, symbols of guilt and sin.

07:00.066 --> 07:08.517
And snow and wool, it represents the purest, brightest whites anyone could imagine, symbols of forgiveness and restoration.

07:09.078 --> 07:13.103
It is humanly impossible to reverse scarlet on wool.

07:13.784 --> 07:22.095
Yet God says, what you cannot do, I will, I will forgive, I will restore, I will rescue, I will cleanse.

07:22.876 --> 07:27.602
The question, of course, was how did God plan to accomplish this impossible rescue?

07:28.002 --> 07:32.328
Several chapters later, Isaiah answers it with a prophecy that changed everything.

07:32.929 --> 07:57.426
Isaiah 9, 2, and 6 says, Every one of us knows what darkness feels like.

07:57.890 --> 08:00.112
both in the natural and in our lives.

08:00.733 --> 08:04.797
Many, if not most of us, walked in today carrying some form of it.

08:05.317 --> 08:12.744
Sometimes it's darkness we created, sometimes it's darkness that found us, and sometimes it is darkness that simply settled in over time.

08:13.445 --> 08:15.887
And that darkness, it can settle anywhere.

08:16.388 --> 08:20.291
In our minds, in our emotions, or even deep in our spirit.

08:20.932 --> 08:25.056
But here's the message of Isaiah and the real meaning of Christmas.

08:25.516 --> 08:27.218
No matter how deep the darkness,

08:27.362 --> 08:29.144
God's light can break through.

08:29.244 --> 08:34.130
No matter how deep the crimson stain, God's grace can make us wide again.

08:34.511 --> 08:37.254
You may be thinking, Mark, you don't understand.

08:37.875 --> 08:39.016
You don't know what I have done.

08:39.076 --> 08:40.598
You don't know what was done to me.

08:40.879 --> 08:41.659
Hear me today.

08:41.700 --> 08:48.388
You can stand on this promise because that prophecy in Isaiah, it wasn't just spoken, it was fulfilled.

08:48.928 --> 08:56.818
Matthew 121, she will get birth to a son and you are to give him the name Jesus because he will save his people

08:56.898 --> 08:58.140
from their sins.

08:58.480 --> 09:04.688
His name is Jesus, the promised Messiah, the Lamb of God, the Savior of the world.

09:05.089 --> 09:10.896
God wrapped Himself in flesh because His love for us would not let Him remain distant.

09:10.916 --> 09:13.219
He saw our sin, our hurt, our brokenness.

09:13.259 --> 09:14.361
He saw the stain.

09:15.062 --> 09:16.183
We could never remove.

09:16.704 --> 09:19.908
And in His great mercy, He refused to leave us as we were.

09:20.529 --> 09:21.630
So He came to rescue.

09:21.971 --> 09:22.892
He came to redeem.

09:23.393 --> 09:24.434
He came to save.

09:24.994 --> 09:31.020
Maybe right now you find yourself lost in life, wandering, unsure of what to do next or what your future holds.

09:31.600 --> 09:33.802
Isaiah tells us exactly who Jesus is.

09:33.862 --> 09:36.465
He is your wonderful counselor.

09:36.945 --> 09:41.349
Life can feel overwhelming for all of us and the questions often outnumber the answers.

09:41.950 --> 09:45.833
Confusion may describe our situation, but it does not define our identity.

09:46.394 --> 09:54.962
Jesus came as the wonderful counselor, the one who guides, the one who speaks truth, the one who steps into our circumstances and walks with us through them.

09:55.234 --> 09:59.338
For some of us, we're facing a situation we simply cannot fix on our own.

10:00.099 --> 10:01.280
He is your mighty God.

10:02.001 --> 10:10.790
Mighty God in the moments that are just too big for us, the addictions we can't break, the wounds we can't heal, the fears we can't silence, the mountains we can't move.

10:11.370 --> 10:18.778
Romans 811 tells us that when we know God, the same power that would end up raising Christ from the dead now lives in us.

10:19.339 --> 10:22.802
He came to carry what we cannot carry, to fight what we cannot fight,

10:23.138 --> 10:26.863
to accomplish what we can never accomplish on our own, He is mighty God.

10:27.583 --> 10:35.593
You know, during this time of year, so many of us experience loneliness, the feeling of being alone, unseen, or disconnected, even when surrounded by others.

10:36.294 --> 10:39.278
If that is you, He is your everlasting Father.

10:40.079 --> 10:45.085
One of the greatest promises Jesus gives us is that when we belong to Him, we are never alone.

10:45.566 --> 10:52.274
Through Him, we experience the love of a perfect heavenly Father, a Father who sees us, who knows us completely,

10:52.418 --> 10:57.563
and who loves us with a love that never fades, never weakens, and never runs out.

10:58.263 --> 11:07.973
And finally, if any part of your life is overwhelmed with anxiety, fear, or inner chaos, and honestly, that is likely true for all of us in some way, hold on to this promise.

11:08.813 --> 11:22.226
He is your prince of peace, not a prince of chaos, not a prince of distraction, the prince of peace, a peace that isn't based on circumstances, emotions, understanding, or control, but on his presence.

11:22.466 --> 11:24.949
wherever Jesus reigns, peace rules.

11:25.510 --> 11:30.337
His peace is a peace we can all have today, no matter what is going on around us.

11:31.018 --> 11:36.365
Wonderful counselor, mighty God, everlasting father, prince of peace.

11:37.086 --> 11:42.574
His name is Jesus because he came to save us, not just in the moment of salvation, but in every way.

11:43.175 --> 11:45.799
He turns scarlet and crimson into snow and wool.

11:45.859 --> 11:48.242
He brings light into our darkness.

11:48.706 --> 11:55.292
This past week, I asked some of our campus pastors to send a text to people across our Highlands locations with one simple question.

11:56.033 --> 11:58.095
What has Jesus saved you from?

11:58.135 --> 11:59.457
It's a great question.

11:59.837 --> 12:08.285
And my prayer is that as you hear some of their responses, it will not only encourage you, but it will build your faith for what God wants to do in your life.

12:08.826 --> 12:13.090
Kaitlyn shared, Jesus saved me from the trauma of my childhood.

12:13.570 --> 12:17.394
For Jeff, it was rescue from a hardened heart and bitterness.

12:17.570 --> 12:21.554
Jesus saved Susan from a lonely and unanchored life.

12:22.075 --> 12:24.698
He saved Bella from all-consuming anxiety.

12:24.978 --> 12:30.444
In Jesus, Michael experienced salvation from the crushing weight of shame and guilt.

12:30.844 --> 12:35.349
And Jesus rescued Jackson from emptiness and chasing the world's view of success.

12:36.250 --> 12:42.597
As I read through those answers and dozens more, I couldn't help but celebrate the goodness of our God.

12:43.258 --> 12:44.139
But hear me today.

12:44.639 --> 12:47.282
His goodness is not just for others, it is for you.

12:47.682 --> 12:55.211
God is ready to step into your story, your struggle, your situation, and bring the healing, hope, and rescue you are longing for.

12:56.032 --> 12:59.676
So how do we experience our Savior this Christmas?

13:00.257 --> 13:07.646
Jeremiah 29, 13 says, you will seek me and you will find me when you seek me with all of your heart.

13:08.347 --> 13:11.891
The truth is God doesn't force himself into our lives.

13:12.692 --> 13:15.275
Scripture says he stands at the door and knocks.

13:16.116 --> 13:17.618
He comes where he is welcomed.

13:18.242 --> 13:19.924
He moves in where he is invited.

13:20.565 --> 13:23.188
He fills the life that makes room for him.

13:23.769 --> 13:26.192
We will find him when we seek him.

13:26.833 --> 13:29.816
And that brings me to something we do every Christmas here at Highlands.

13:30.237 --> 13:36.765
If you've been around for any amount of time, you know that we reveal our focus for the coming year during these services.

13:37.265 --> 13:40.229
For months, I've been asking God to give me a word for 2026.

13:41.270 --> 13:43.653
And instead of just a word, he gave me a verse.

13:44.094 --> 13:47.698
A verse we will memorize and declare all year long.

13:47.874 --> 13:55.984
Matthew 633, but seek first his kingdom and his righteousness and all these things will be given to you as well.

13:56.465 --> 13:59.509
Highlands, here's our 2026 rally cry.

13:59.969 --> 14:07.539
We seek God first, first in our day, first in our relationships, first in our finances, first in our lives.

14:08.280 --> 14:10.963
Seeking God first isn't how we earn his blessing.

14:11.664 --> 14:16.370
It's how we position ourselves to receive everything he already has for us.

14:16.642 --> 14:20.529
When we put God first in our priorities, He will order our steps.

14:20.949 --> 14:24.575
When we put Him first in our decisions, He will give us wisdom and clarity.

14:25.056 --> 14:29.143
When we put Him first in our relationships, He will bring healing and strength.

14:29.263 --> 14:32.328
When we put Him first in our finances, He will provide.

14:32.388 --> 14:36.355
And when we put Him first in our days, He will fill our lives with peace.

14:36.415 --> 14:37.076
So come on.

14:37.657 --> 14:42.866
In 2026, let's truly seek God first.

14:43.202 --> 14:48.187
If you're new here, I want to invite you to go all in with us and give us one year of your life.

14:48.427 --> 14:50.809
We actually call it the one year challenge.

14:51.310 --> 14:51.950
Attend church.

14:52.331 --> 14:53.532
Join us for 21 days.

14:53.972 --> 14:54.873
Get in a small group.

14:54.893 --> 14:55.854
Discover your purpose.

14:56.155 --> 14:56.755
Serve others.

14:57.316 --> 14:57.976
Make a difference.

14:58.056 --> 15:05.363
And if you do, 2026 will become the greatest year of your life spiritually and you will never regret it.

15:05.964 --> 15:12.210
But as we prepare to celebrate our 25th anniversary as a church next year, I'm giving the same challenge to all of us.

15:12.578 --> 15:15.001
even those who've been a part of highlands from the very beginning.

15:15.602 --> 15:22.730
I believe year 25 will mark a new season of blessing, calling, and purpose for our church.

15:23.251 --> 15:28.297
A chance for all of us to grow stronger and fall deeper in love with Jesus than ever before.

15:28.897 --> 15:29.979
Don't miss a second of it.

15:30.099 --> 15:32.482
In 2026, God first.

15:33.042 --> 15:33.943
But here's the good news.

15:34.824 --> 15:36.466
We don't have to wait for the new year.

15:37.347 --> 15:39.570
You know, earlier we imagined this field

15:39.906 --> 15:42.670
as the one where the angels appeared to the shepherds.

15:43.170 --> 15:44.171
I mean, think about it.

15:45.153 --> 15:47.335
What an incredible moment that must have been.

15:47.396 --> 15:56.087
They were invited to experience Jesus, but the decision to actually go and seek Him, that was still on them.

15:56.587 --> 15:57.609
It was their decision.

15:58.209 --> 16:02.535
And honestly, 2,000 years later, that's where we find ourselves this Christmas.

16:03.216 --> 16:08.082
Each of us, we're in our own field, our own moment of decision.

16:08.706 --> 16:12.211
God is calling us, will we seek Him?

16:12.952 --> 16:13.853
So here's what we're gonna do.

16:14.314 --> 16:20.222
Before we light candles together, our team is going to sing a song that will allow us to reflect on the message we just heard.

16:21.043 --> 16:21.764
God loves you.

16:22.445 --> 16:26.130
Jesus came to earth on a rescue mission for you.

16:26.170 --> 16:35.604
And as we seek Him in our lives, He will do what only He can do, turn our darkness into light, and the scarlet areas of our lives into wool.

16:36.124 --> 16:37.266
And as the team leads us,

16:37.602 --> 16:43.218
Let's all open our hearts to whatever decision God is calling us to make this Christmas.

